few ideas worth using in your own life. But at its heart, this project is simply here to help you start interrogating what it means to live well as a human being, as a member of your community, or just as yourself. If we accomplish that, we will have succeeded. So, what do you think? What is flourishing in the 21st century?Demetrios Mammas (23C) is the Editorial Board Editor and Ben Thomas (23C) is the Chair of the Editorial Board. Both oversaw“Flourishing in the 21st Century.”[/vc_column_text][vc_separator][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=”1/3″][cq_vc_flipbox frontfullimage=”57387″ backfullimage=”56891″ cardstyle=”bluejeans” link=”url:https%3A%2F%2Femorywheel.com%2Fliving-la-vida-local%2F||target:%20_blank|”][vc_btn title=”Living la vida local” style=”classic” color=”default” align=”center” link=”url:https%3A%2F%2Femorywheel.com%2Fliving-la-vida-local%2F||target:%20_blank|” button_block=”true”][vc_column_text]Without investing in walkable cities, we are failing to invest in ourselves and our cities. For my last year at Emory, I will cherish the closeness I have with my friends. When I leave, I will look for a city where I can create the same intimacy I have found at Emory.By Rachel Broun (23C)[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=”1/3″][cq_vc_flipbox frontfullimage=”44286″ backfullimage=”53189″ link=”url:https%3A%2F%2Femorywheel.com%2Fcollege-isnt-always-the-best-four-years-it-shouldnt-have-to-be%2F||target:%20_blank|”][vc_btn title=”College isn’t always “the best four years.” It shouldn’t have to be.” style=”classic” color=”default” align=”center” link=”url:https%3A%2F%2Femorywheel.com%2Fcollege-isnt-always-the-best-four-years-it-shouldnt-have-to-be%2F||target:%20_blank|” button_block=”true”][vc_column_text]College might not always be the best four years you’ve ever spent, but why should it be? Maybe the golden moments of college life are what you remember when you look back. Maybe the best years are still to come.By Chaya Tong (25C)[/vc_colum