g to engage with those we disagree with, and we have to get more comfortable with tough, uncomfortable subjects if we are to acknowledge our hypocrisy and then do something about it.By Jake Busch (22C)[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=”1/4″][cq_vc_flipbox frontfullimage=”57495″ backfullimage=”55752″ link=”url:https%3A%2F%2Femorywheel.com%2Freclaim-your-life-be-present%2F||target:%20_blank|”][vc_btn title=”Reclaim your life, be present” style=”classic” color=”default” align=”center” link=”url:https%3A%2F%2Femorywheel.com%2Freclaim-your-life-be-present%2F||target:%20_blank|” button_block=”true”][vc_column_text]My defense of mindfulness as a small practice with a large impact does not come from a place of minimizing other stressors in life. Rather, it acts a tool that better equips us with the fulfillment to better tackle them.By Dani Parra del Riego (25C)[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=”1/4″][cq_vc_flipbox frontfullimage=”57665″ backfullimage=”45994″ link=”url:https%3A%2F%2Femorywheel.com%2Fflourishing-as-a-latinx-woman-at-emory%2F||target:%20_blank|”][vc_btn title=”Flourishing as a Latinx woman at Emory” style=”classic” color=”default” align=”center” link=”url:https%3A%2F%2Femorywheel.com%2Fflourishing-as-a-latinx-woman-at-emory%2F||target:%20_blank|” button_block=”true”][vc_column_text]Instead of getting discouraged, I have managed to use this pressure to remind myself of the importance of proving Latinx women are capable of more than what the patriarchy expects from us.By Sara Perez (24C)[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]Designed byElegant Themes| Powered byWordPressAdvertiseClassifiedsArchivesJob BoardHave The Wheel delivered to your inbox!Get The Wheel delivered to your inbox!Your information will *never* be shared or sold to a 3rd party.